President Donald J. Trump has promoted Sarah Sanders to the role of White House Press Secretary. Sanders, who previously served as Deputy Press Secretary, will now be the President's principal spokesperson and head of the White House Press Office. President Trump praised Sanders for her outstanding job in getting his administration's message out to the American people. Sanders expressed her gratitude for the honor and her excitement to continue promoting the President's agenda. She also mentioned her appreciation for Sean Spicer, who has been a colleague, friend, and mentor. Sanders is looking forward to working with the new Communications Director, Anthony Scaramucci.